#OurEarth: Innovation in Exploration Hangout
Mon, April 22, 12:00 PM
Created by National Geographic
+
45
7
8
7
Watch Again: National Geographic brought together leaders from +NASA, +Catlin Seaview Survey, and +National Geographic using the newest technology to explore and conserve our Earth.

* * * *

We're continuing to celebrate Earth Day with a week's worth of Hangouts with experts, communitiesand some more National Geographic explorers. See what's scheduled for the rest of the #OurEarth series.

Updated Upcoming Hangouts:

How can you make a global difference by recycling? Join +Earth911, +Mother Nature Network, and community Reduce, Reuse, Recycle on Thursday, April 25 at 2 p.m. ET (7 p.m. UTC).

RSVP for the event: http://bit.ly/17Y1MFH

The last Hangout in the #OurEarth series brings together experts from +The TerraMar Project to discuss ocean conservation on Friday, April 26 at 2 p.m. ET (7 p.m. UTC).

RSVP for the event: http://bit.ly/ZJApM5

Want to ask any of the explorers a question? Post comments on Google+ with #OurEarth.

 * * * *

Past Hangouts:

Chasing deadly storms, studying life on the Great Barrier Reef, monitoring Earth from the sky: Technology allows explorers to go to new extremes and discover more about our world. Join National Geographic for a live Hangout on Earth Day, April 22 at 12 p.m. ET (5 p.m. UTC, April 23 at 2 a.m. AEST) to celebrate innovation in exploration.

Did you miss this Hangout? Watch it here: http://bit.ly/ZJBrI7

Join experts from the Water community and +WHOLE WORLD Water as well as National Geographic Explorer Sanda Postel to discuss what can be done about the global water crisis on Tuesday, April 23 at 2 p.m. ET ( 7 p.m. UTC).

Did you miss this Hangout? Watch it here: http://bit.ly/ZKGFQM

Can we learn from Nature's Engineers? National Geographic Explorer Amy Dickman, experts from +Zoo Atlanta, and Director of Herpetological Research Joe Mendelson will join the Hangout to discuss their favorite Engineers of Nature on Wednesday, April 24 at 4 p.m. ET (9 p.m. UTC).  

Did you miss this Hangout? Watch it here: http://bit.ly/11lgqBU

Find out more about the #OurEarth Hangout series: http://on.natgeo.com/116wNSN
Official website:http://on.natgeo.com/12FcJvG
